#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 MOKOPANE - President Cyril Ramaphosa launched Anglo American’s hydrogen-powered ultra-class mine haul truck in Limpopo on Friday. Ramaphosa says the country is committed to taking the necessary steps to fight climate change. READ: WATCH: Ramaphosa opens brick factory The nuGen Zero Emissions Haulage Solution uses hydrogen produced on-site in conjunction with a battery to operate. As part of South Africa's commitment to transition to a low carbon economy and climate-resilient society, this innovation will help the country fulfill its pledge. Watch the video above for more details on this story.